Hewlett Packard Enterprise (HPE) has appointed President Ntuli as the Managing Director for HPE South Africa effective from 1 August 2019. Ntuli joined HPE South Africa from Dimension Data MEA, where he held the position of Regional Executive of Sales in South-East Africa. Before joining Dimension Data, he spent over six years at HPE leading the Servers’ Business Unit and serving in various sales manager roles. “Ntuli has over 18 years’ experience in IT and brings with him a wealth of expertise,” said HPE. Ntuli will be responsible for overseeing a broad hardware, software and services portfolio, the company said.